                            <comment id="13140596" author="jukkaz" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2011 21:48:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is now pretty much done. Details in CHANGES.txt:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OSGi: The tika-core bundle will now automatically pick up and use any available Parser and Detector services when deployed to an OSGi environment. The tika-parsers bundle provides such services based on for all the supported file formats for which the upstream parser library is available. If you don&apos;t want to track all the parser libraries as separate OSGi bundles, you can use the tika-bundle bundle that packages tika-parsers together with all its upstream dependencies. (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-565&quot; title=&quot;Improved OSGi bundling&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
